\f2\i \cf0 Hey Vedika,
\f0\i0 \

\f2\i I\'92ve been thinking a lot about us \'97 about everything we\'92ve been through over the past six years. I want to be honest and open with you because you deserve that. First, I want to say I\'92m truly sorry. Sorry for the times I hurt you, for my mistakes \'97 even the ones I didn\'92t mean to make. I know some of those mistakes caused you pain, made you doubt me, made you question us. I take full responsibility for that. I never wanted to be the source of your struggle or sadness.
\f0\i0 \

\f2\i I\'92ve fought so many battles for us \'97 with myself, with my family, even with the world around me \'97 because I believe in you and us. You\'92re not just someone I love; you\'92re the person I want to build my life with. I can\'92t imagine a life without you in it. But I know love isn\'92t just about holding on tightly; it\'92s about understanding, growing, and sometimes giving space.
\f0\i0 \

\f2\i Right now, I know things are hard between us. You asked me to leave, to stay away because you feel I\'92m hurting you. That breaks me. But I want you to know I\'92m not going anywhere \'97 not because I\'92m ignoring your feelings, but because I truly believe we can heal and grow if we both try.
\f0\i0 \

\f2\i I admire you so much, Vedika. You\'92re incredibly smart, strong, and driven. Getting into IIM Udaipur for your MBA \'97 that was no small feat. I\'92m proud of you every single day. And now, I want to help you take the next big step \'97 finding a job, becoming independent, paying your fees on your own, and standing tall with your own strength \'97 I want to help you prepare for all this. Not because I think you can\'92t do it on your own, because I truly believe you are more than capable of handling everything by yourself. You\'92re incredibly strong and smart. But I want to be there with you \'97 not to take over, but to walk beside you as your partner, sharing the journey, supporting you through the challenges, and celebrating your successes together. Because life is better when we face it together, and I want to be the one who stands with you, not behind or in front, but right beside you.
\f0\i0 \

\f2\i I know I\'92ve asked for chances before, and I\'92m ashamed to ask again. But I want you to understand this isn\'92t about me needing you \'97 it\'92s about me wanting to be the man worthy of you. I want to be better, for you and for myself. I\'92m working on my mistakes, my fears, and my weaknesses every day. I want to be the partner who lifts you up, not the one who weighs you down.
\f0\i0 \

\f2\i I realize sometimes love means stepping back, listening more, and letting you heal in your own time. So I promise to respect your space, to be patient, and to be ready when you want to talk or lean on me again.
\f0\i0 \

\f2\i Until then, let\'92s just keep joining calls and studying together. I\'92m not doing this to make up for the mess I\'92ve created, but so that our professional goals don\'92t get impacted, and also to keep myself alive and connected in this tough time.
\f0\i0 \

\f2\i You once told me I was hurting you, and I don\'92t want to be that person anymore. I want to be your safe place. The one you trust completely. The one who supports your dreams no matter what.
\f0\i0 \

\f2\i If you ever doubt your worth or your strength, remember I see the incredible woman you are \'97 not just for your achievements but for your heart, your kindness, and your courage.
\f0\i0 \

\f2\i I love you, Vedika. I always have. And even if life takes us on different paths, that love will never fade. But if you\'92re willing to let me walk beside you, to heal and grow together, I promise to give you all of me \'97 patient, understanding, and stronger than ever.
\f0\i0 \

\f2\i Take all the time you need. I\'92ll be here \'97 quietly, steadily, hoping for us.
\f0\i0 \

\f2\i With all my heart,
\f0\i0 \uc0\u8232 
\f2\i Deepka
