Vedika,\
I don\'92t even know where to begin, because honestly, I\'92m scared. Scared of losing you. Scared of what I\'92ve done. Scared of what the silence between us might mean. I\'92ve been sitting with this pain, this guilt, this storm inside me \'97 and it\'92s tearing me apart. But today, I just want to say everything. Not as an excuse. Not to convince you of anything. But because you deserve to hear the truth \'97 raw, honest, unfiltered \'97 from the person who loves you more than anything else in this world.\
Yes, I made mistakes. I hurt you \'97 maybe more than I even realized at the time. Not with intention, never with the desire to cause you pain \'97 but the outcome is the same, and I take full responsibility for it. I was immature at moments, reactive, insecure, and at times lost in emotions that I didn\'92t know how to handle. You stood by me for so long, gave me so many chances, and each time I promised to be better. But in moments, I faltered. And I know that faltering has shaken your trust, your peace, your love.\
And still \'97 despite all of that \'97 I am standing here today and saying, with every fiber of who I am: I want to make this right. Not because I think it\'92ll be easy. Not because I think one message can fix it. But because I know that what we have is 
\f2\i real
\f0\i0 . It is deep. It is sacred. And it is worth fighting for.\
Vedika, you\'92re not just someone I love. You are my only person. My mirror. My anchor. My dream. From that first moment when I saw you in college, sitting in the lobby, radiating so much intelligence, grace, and presence \'97 something inside me shifted. I didn\'92t even have the courage to speak properly. I stuttered. I mumbled. I walked away thinking someone like you could never look my way. But that very moment planted the seed for everything I\'92ve worked for since. You made me want to become better \'97 not to win you, but to feel worthy of even standing near you.\
And over time, somehow, life gave me a chance. We connected. We spoke. We laughed. We fell. I still remember our late-night chats, your sarcasm, your fierce clarity, your determination \'97 and the way you made me feel seen. Heard. Loved.\
Vedika, I\'92ve seen your heart. You are not just brilliant \'97 you are kind. You are strong, but also soft. You\'92ve fought your own battles, carried burdens silently, and still had the strength to hold mine too. And now, you're at a turning point \'97 your MBA at IIM Udaipur, your dreams lining up before you \'97 and I want to walk with you through it. Not as a crutch. Not as a distraction. But as someone who genuinely wants to 
\f2\i stand beside you
\f0\i0  in your success and celebrate every single milestone with you.\
Let me be crystal clear here:\uc0\u8232 You do 
\f1\b not
\f0\b0  need me to succeed. You are perfectly capable of doing it all on your own. I\'92ve seen your grit, your late-night study sessions, the fire in your voice when you speak of your goals.\uc0\u8232 But I want to be there. Because I believe love isn\'92t about completing someone \'97 it\'92s about choosing to stand with them through every chapter. I want to teach you what I know, help you prepare for interviews, cheer you on during tough days \'97 not to make up for my mess, but because I love you that deeply. Because helping you 
\f2\i doesn't feel like a duty
\f0\i0  \'97 it feels like a privilege.\
And about the calls \'97 yes, let\'92s keep joining them. Let\'92s keep studying together. Not to pretend things are normal, but to ensure our pain doesn\'92t destroy our dreams. I\'92m not doing this to earn back your love or to \'93buy\'94 forgiveness. I\'92m doing it because I don\'92t want our personal setbacks to derail the extraordinary future you\'92re building \'97 and because seeing you, hearing your voice, even in silence \'97 it\'92s what keeps me breathing right now.\
I know you love me too, even if it\'92s buried under hurt and anger right now. I know it in the way you used to say my name when you were excited, the way your voice softened when I was anxious, and the way you always believed in me even when I didn\'92t believe in myself. That love \'97 it hasn\'92t vanished. I know it\'92s still there. Right now, maybe you also hate me \'97 for breaking what was beautiful. But that hate only exists because the love was once so strong.\
Vedika, this isn\'92t me begging. This isn\'92t about asking for one last chance. This is me telling you, with complete honesty \'97 
\f1\b I want this chance
\f0\b0 . I 
\f2\i need
\f0\i0  this chance. Because there is no \'93me\'94 without \'93us.\'94 Because it\'92s either you in my life or no life at all. I\'92ve fought my own family for this love. I\'92ve cried in silence more nights than I can count. And even now, despite all the chaos, despite how far it feels \'97 my heart still whispers your name.\
You are the home I never knew I needed.\uc0\u8232 You are the future I still believe in.\u8232 And this \'97 this is not the end. Not if I have anything to say about it.\
Take time if you need to. Breathe. Heal. But remember this \'97 I\'92m still here. Not perfect, but present. Not flawless, but faithful. Not demanding, but deeply, deeply devoted.\
And when you're ready \'97 even just to talk, to study, to sit in silence \'97 I\'92ll be here, waiting. Always.\
With a heart that has only ever belonged to you,\uc0\u8232 
\f1\b Deepak
